title: Use Parsec Mock for testing
body:
This commit changes the CI script to start Parsec Mock there. Moves the
ping test from the already existing mock interface to Parsec Mock.

In the future the tests in `src/core/testing` can be added in the Parsec Mock repo and used from the `mock_service.rs` test file. That way the test cases can benefit all clients.

title: Implement provider and auth bootstrapping
body:
This commit implements bootstrapping of the `BasicClient`. Previously,
the client would be initialised without any implicit provider and
with a mandatory authentication value. Now the client can be initialised
with default values for both, with a conditional parameter required for
the case when direct authentication is in use.

Signed-off-by: Ionut Mihalcea <ionut.mihalcea@arm.com>

title: Add Unix Peer Credential auth support
body:
This commit adds support for authentication using Unix Peer Credentials.
This involves the library automatically populating the `Auth` field of
every request with a serialized version of the UID.

Closes #41

title: Remove filesystem checks
body:
This commit removes the filesystem checks for correct permissions on
Parsec "assets". The checks can now be removed because the new locations
in the filesystem mean that only a privileged user can create the files.

Fixes #51
